##
## "Print Ahnentafel Chart"
##

@NODE PrintAhnentafel "Print Ahnentafel Chart"
Print/Print Ahnentafel Chart:

This menu item will print an Ahnentafel Chart for the current person.

The information contained in an Ahnentafel Chart can be as short as a name
or as long as a paragraph.  Because an Ahnentafel Chart is a list it can be
very compact.  Many pages of pedigrees can be printed on just a few pages
in the Ahnentafel format.

NOTE: Sex-less people will "break" Ahnentafel Charts. Hence nobody will
      appear "above" sexless people.

Printing can be aborted at any time.

Example:
=======

Ahnentafel Chart: Hamilton Robert SMITH

Project Name: Example
Report Printed On: 17 Jan 1998                                    Page: 1
=========================================================================
1   Hamilton Robert SMITH [2]. Born: 14 Feb 1919, Invercargill, NZ. 
---------------------------------- II -----------------------------------
2   Donald Gordon SMITH [4]. Born: 3 Jun 1879, Pleasant Creek, Victoria,
    Australia. Died: 14 Feb 1960, Christchurch, NZ. Buried: Park
    Cemetery, Rangiora, NZ. Married: 17 May 1913, St Paul's Methodist
    Parsonage, Invercargill [FGRN 4]....
3   Caroline Mary MATHEWS [5]. Born: Aug 1879?, Thomastown, Victoria,
    Australia. Died: 3 Mar 1962, Coronation Hospital, Christchurch, NZ.
    Buried: 5 Mar 1962, Park Cemetery, Rangiora, NZ. 
---------------------------------- III ----------------------------------
4   Charles Alfred SMITH [6]. Born: 9 Apr 1848, Musselburgh, SCT. Died:
    1907, Stawell, Victoria, Australia. Married: 1869, Wesleyan Methodist
    Church, Ballarat W., VIC [FGRN 7]....
5   Margaret DONALD [7]. Born: 15 Mar 1850, Farm near Fort William, SCT.
    Died: 1946, Stawell, Victoria, Australia. 
6   Robert John MATHEWS [8]. Born: ~1838, Dublin, Ireland. Died: 28 Sep
    1891, Fitzroy, Bourke, VIC, Australia. Buried: 30 Sep 1891, Coburg
    Cemetery. Married: 5 Dec 1867, Moyston, near Ararat, VIC, Australia
    [FGRN 2]....
7   Eliza Ann WILSON [9]. Born: ~1845, County Monaghan, Ireland. Died: 7
    Jan 1911, South Preston, Bourke, VIC, Australia. Buried: 9 Jan 1911,
    Coburg Cemetery. 
---------------------------------- IV -----------------------------------
8   Charles SMITH [60]. ...
9   Selina Julia BLISS [61]. 

...etc...

An explanation of the numbering scheme in Ahnentafel Charts -
===========================================================

The starting person is given the number 1.  Their father is 2, and their
mother is 3.  Number 2's father is 4 and his mother is 5.  Number 3's
father is 6 and her mother is 7.
          
To generalize: Double any person's number to get their father's number.
Double any person's number and add one to get their mother's number.  Note
that (after the first generation), all the males have even numbers, and all
the females have odd numbers.  Ahnentafel numbers need not be consecutive -
if an ancestor is unkown, their number is simply omitted from the list.

Each generation is indicated by a roman numeral. For example, 'IV'
indicates that the following people are the fourth generation 'higher' than
the starting person. 

@ENDNODE

##
## "Print Forefathers Chart"
##

@NODE PrintForefathers "Print Forefathers Chart"
Print/Print Forefathers Chart:

This is a specialised version of the @{" Ahnentafel " LINK PrintAhnentafel} that prints details of a
person's forefathers (males) only, along with details of their spouses.

NOTE: Sex-less people will "break" Forefathers Charts. Hence nobody will
      appear "above" sexless people.

Printing can be aborted at any time.

Example:
=======

Forefathers Chart: Hamilton Robert SMITH

Project Name: Example
Report Printed On: 17 Jan 1998                                    Page: 1
=========================================================================
I      Hamilton Robert SMITH [2]. Born: 14 Feb 1919, Invercargill, NZ. 

II     Donald Gordon SMITH [4]. Born: 3 Jun 1879, Pleasant Creek,
       Victoria, Australia. Died: 14 Feb 1960, Christchurch, NZ. Buried:
       Park Cemetery, Rangiora, NZ. 

       Spouse: Caroline Mary MATHEWS [5]. Born: Aug 1879?, Thomastown,
       Victoria, Australia. Died: 3 Mar 1962, Coronation Hospital,
       Christchurch, NZ. Buried: 5 Mar 1962, Park Cemetery, Rangiora, NZ.
       Married: 17 May 1913, St Paul's Methodist Parsonage, Invercargill
       [FGRN 4].

III    Charles Alfred SMITH [6]. Born: 9 Apr 1848, Musselburgh, SCT.
       Died: 1907, Stawell, Victoria, Australia. 

       Spouse: Margaret DONALD [7]. Born: 15 Mar 1850, Farm near Fort
       William, SCT. Died: 1946, Stawell, Victoria, Australia. Married:
       1869, Wesleyan Methodist Church, Ballarat W., VIC [FGRN 7].

IV     Charles SMITH [60]. 

       Spouse: Selina Julia BLISS [61]. 
@ENDNODE

##
## "Print Descendant Chart"
##

@NODE PrintDescendant "Print Descendant Chart"
Print/Print Descendant Chart:

This menu item will print a Descendant Chart for the current person.

Charts are limited to 32 generations (about 600 years by most
calculations). If there are more generations than can reasonably fit across
the page, the additional descendants (not printed) are indicated by ">>>".

This chart is a "summary" chart showing only the names of descendants. For
complete details of all descendants, use the @{" Print Progeny Chart " LINK PrintProgeny} option.

Printing can be aborted at any time.

Example:
=======

Descendant Chart: Charles Alfred SMITH

Project Name: Example
Report Printed On: 17 Jan 1998                                    Page: 1
=========================================================================
1   2   3   4   5   6   
+---+---+---+---+---+----------------------------------------------------
Charles Alfred SMITH [6]
s:Margaret DONALD [7]
    Selina Mary SMITH [34]
    s:William DOBSON [40]
    Charles Henry (Harry) SMITH [35]
    s:Mary ANDERSON [41]
    |   Donald SMITH [49]
    |   s:Joyce CASTLE [51]
