    |   Mollie SMITH [48]
    |   s:Cecil LAWSON [50]
    Edith Elvira SMITH [36]
    s:William Henry CARTER [42]

... etc ...
@ENDNODE

##
## "Print Progeny Chart"
##

@NODE PrintProgeny "Print Progeny Chart"
Print/Print Progeny Chart:

This menu item will print a Progeny Chart for the current person.

Printing can be aborted at any time.

Example:
=======

Progeny Chart: Charles Alfred SMITH

Project Name: Example
Report Printed On: 17 Jan 1998                                    Page: 1
=========================================================================

----------------------------------- I -----------------------------------

1  Charles Alfred SMITH [6]. Born: 9 Apr 1848, Musselburgh, SCT. Died:
   1907, Stawell, Victoria, Australia. 

   Spouse: Margaret DONALD [7]. Born: 15 Mar 1850, Farm near Fort
   William, SCT. Died: 1946, Stawell, Victoria, Australia. Married: 1869,
   Wesleyan Methodist Church, Ballarat W., VIC [FGRN 7].

        2.a Selina Mary SMITH [34]. Born: 1871, Pleasant Creek, VIC.
            Died: ~1923, Stawell, VIC. 
       +3.b Charles Henry (Harry) SMITH [35]. Born: 1873, Pleasant Creek,
            VIC. Died: 12 Sep 1947, Blenheim, NZ. Buried: Veteran's
            Cemetery, Blenheim, NZ. 
        4.c Edith Elvira SMITH [36]. Born: 1875, Stawell, VIC. Died:
            Stawell, VIC. 
       +5.d Ernest Alfred SMITH [37]. Born: 8 Jan 1877, Pleasant Creek,
            VIC. Died: 17 Jun 1953, Christchurch, NZ. Buried: Linwood
            Crematorium, Christchurch, NZ. 
       +6.e Donald Gordon SMITH [4]. Born: 3 Jun 1879, Pleasant Creek,
            Victoria, Australia. Died: 14 Feb 1960, Christchurch, NZ.
            Buried: Park Cemetery, Rangiora, NZ. 
       +7.f Edgar Eric SMITH [38]. Born: 6 Apr 1883, Stawell, VIC. 
        8.g Victor Arthur SMITH [89]. Born: 6 Apr 1883, Stawell, VIC. 
        9.h Flora Maggie SMITH [39]. Born: 1888, Stawell, VIC. 

---------------------------------- II -----------------------------------

3  Charles Henry (Harry) SMITH [35]. Born: 1873, Pleasant Creek, VIC.
   Died: 12 Sep 1947, Blenheim, NZ. Buried: Veteran's Cemetery, Blenheim,
   NZ. 

   Spouse: Mary ANDERSON [41]. Born: 1 Sep 1882, Gippsland, VIC. Died: 31
   Mar 1958, Hastings, NZ. Buried: Hastings, NZ. Married: 10 Sep 1908,
   Presbyterian Church of Victoria, Malvern, V [FGRN 9].

       10.a Donald SMITH [49]. Born: 12 Aug 1910, Stawell, VIC. Died:
            1968, Sussex, ENGLAND. 
       11.b Margaret SMITH [45]. Born: 9 Jun 1913, Stawell, VIC. 
       12.c Mollie SMITH [48]. Born: 27 Apr 1915, Stawell, VIC. 

... etc...

An explanation of the numbering scheme in Progeny Charts -
========================================================

The numbering system used in the Progeny Charts is a variation on the
'Register System (NEHGR)' first used in the New England Historical and
Genealogical Register, and is closely related to the 'Record System (NGS)'
developed by the National Genealogical Society.

In this variant, every person receives a 'Register Number', a number
indicating the line of descent, followed by their children in numerical
order. The starting person will always receive the Register Number of 1,
and their children will be numbered 2, 3, etc. Every child also receives a
letter (a, b, c, etc) indicating the birth order.

Except for the starting person, every person will appear first as a child.

Any child whose Register Number is preceded by a '+' sign, is also repeated
as an adult. Even though a child may have a Register Number, if no '+' sign
appears, that will be the last time that person will be seen in the
descendancy.

Note that only the blood-line descendants of that starting person receive a
Register Number. Spouses of descendants are not part of the descendancy and
do not receive a number.

@ENDNODE

##
## "Print List of Families"
##

@NODE PrintFamilies "Print List of Families"
Print/Print List of Families:

This menu item will print a list of the families currently defined in the
database. Lists can either be printed in numerical order (by FGRN), in
male's name alphabetical order, female's name alphabetical order, or
in Wedding (plus engagement) Date order.

NOTE: Male partners are always displayed in the left-hand column and
      females partners in the right-hand column if at all possible.

When the list is sorted by Wedding Date, some lines may end up with
(apparently) no date. This is because the Wedding Date order list is sorted
by wedding AND engagement date. Therefore, if there is no wedding date but
there IS an engagement date, the person is collated by the engagement date,
but when printed out the wedding date doesn't exist, and the "Married"
field of the report will be empty. Hence the apparent 'strange' sorting.
Observe the report title - it says that the names are sorted by
'wedding/engagement', NOT just wedding date.

Printing can be aborted at any time.

Example:
=======

List of Families (Order: Male's Name)

Project Name: Example
Report Printed On: 17 Jan 1998                                    Page: 1
=========================================================================
FGRN Male's Name            IRN Female's Name          IRN        Married
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
33   ADAMS, David James     104 SMITH, Margaret Ellen  103    11 Sep 1948
34   ADAMS, Paul Raymond    105 WATSON, Sarah          106    23 Apr 1976
16   ANDERSON, Robert        52 RAMAGE, Mary            53               
32   CARRINGTON, Walter     100 SMITH, Edith            98    28 Nov 1942
10   CARTER, William Henry   42 SMITH, Edith Elvira     36           1903
8    DOBSON, William         40 SMITH, Selina Mary      34           1891

... etc ...
@ENDNODE

##
## "Print Family Group Sheet"
##

@NODE PrintFGS "Print Family Group Sheet"
Print/Print Family Group Sheet (FGS):

This menu item will print a Family Group Sheet containing all the
information in the database about the specified family.

The "Current" option will print a Family Group Sheet for the current
family.

The "Selected..." option will display a requester where you can select the
families you wish to print FGS's for. Note that this requester has a menu
that allows you to select all the families displayed in the list. This is
useful for printing all the items in a "filtered" list.

The "All" option will print Family Group Sheets for all families in the
database.

If the "Print attached note" option in the @{" Print Options " LINK PrintPrefsReq} requester is
set, the family note file attached to the family will be appended to the
printed report. When printing attached notes, no notice is taken of the
length of the text lines. The lines are simply read directly from the text
file and "dumped" unmodified to the output. That is, the programme will do
no word-wrapping.  Make sure that the text line lengths are <= than the
paper width otherwise the printer will issue apparently spurious carriage
returns. This method of handling also means that notes MUST be written by a
text editor, NOT a word processor!

Printing can be aborted at any time.

